The paper discusses the use of artificial spiking neural networks for processing visual information from a Dynamic Vision Sensor (DVS) and integrating it into a real robotic setup. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Robotics (cs.RO), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Among these, cs.NE is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the use of synaptic plasticity rules for spiking networks, which is a key area of research in neural and evolutionary computing. The other categories are also likely as they relate to the use of visual information for robotics and machine learning applications.
